    <sys:String x:Key="Settings.Language.Label">Language</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Settings.Language.Hint">Restart the app to fully apply the language change in every window.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Settings.Ai.Intro">After each scan, an AI assistant can verify that found updates are genuinely newer than what is installed and flag drivers that may cause problems. It is optional and best-effort: if it is off or unavailable, scans work exactly as before.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Settings.Ai.Provider">Provider</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Settings.Ai.ApiKey">API key</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Settings.Ai.Model">Model</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Settings.Ai.WebSearch">Use live web search to check for the latest version and reported issues</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Settings.Ai.OllamaUrl">Base URL</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Settings.Ai.KeyWarning">The Gemini API key is stored in plain text in settings.json on this computer. Only enable this on a machine you trust.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Settings.Ai.GeminiGuideHeader">How to set up Gemini (free)</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Settings.Ai.GeminiGuideBody">1. Open Google AI Studio (link below) and sign in with a Google account.&#x0a;2. Click "Create API key" and copy the key.&#x0a;3. Paste it into the API key box above.&#x0a;4. Keep the default model (gemini-2.5-flash) or type another Gemini model name.&#x0a;5. Leave web search on so the model can check the newest version and known issues.&#x0a;&#x0a;The free tier is plenty for occasional scans. The key is sent only to Google.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Settings.Ai.OllamaGuideHeader">How to set up Ollama (local, no key)</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Settings.Ai.OllamaGuideBody">1. Download and install Ollama from the link below.&#x0a;2. Open a terminal and run:  ollama pull llama3.1&#x0a;3. Make sure Ollama is running. It listens on http://localhost:11434 by default.&#x0a;4. Keep the default base URL, or change it if Ollama runs elsewhere.&#x0a;5. Type the model you pulled (for example llama3.1) in the model box above.&#x0a;&#x0a;Ollama runs entirely on your PC - no API key and no internet are needed.</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="History.Title">DriverUpdater - History</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="History.Heading">Update history</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="History.Refresh">Refresh</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="History.Rollback">Rollback</sys:String>
